metadata.name: Pinceladas #76
metadata.description:
Pinceladas is spanish for Brush Strokes, which I was trying to emulate using Perlin Noise. I have carefully picked a selection of color palettes, which can vary within strokes. I hope you like what I've created.
The resolution of this piece is 4000x4000, which makes for a nice download. Please note that, due to the high resolution, this piece can a few seconds to load.

metadata.name: MonoSynth: V-MI 001 #39
metadata.description:
*** V-MI 001 is a mono synthesizer design for metaverse and digital worlds.

Click |START THE SOUND| to power the synth, a speaker will appear near to the button. Twig the faders and buttons to change the sound.

A 3 Octave keyboard:
(Capslock should be Off)

Q-W-E-R-T-Y-U-I      
     A-S-D-F-G-H-J-K    
         Z-X-C-V-B-N-M-Ö   
You can assign a scale(Major, Natural Minor and Harmonic Minor) to the keyboard by clicking the |Scale Type| button and monitor it on the screen below.

There are 4 oscillators(Square, Sine, Sawtooth and Triangle) which can be switched by clicking |Wave Type| button and can be monitored with the screen below the button. 

You can change the octave of whole keyboard by clicking the |Octave Up| and |Octave Down| buttons. 

SPECTROGRAM and OSCILLOSCOPE

EFFECTS:        A REVERB which can be controlled by the fader  |———

		A DELAY which can be controlled by the fade  |——— 

		AN ADSR which can be controlled by the four faders below in order of Attack-Decay-Sustain-Release   |———

metadata.name: Mosaic #646
metadata.description:
---
Notes:
- Click to pause/unpause
- The aspect ratio is fixed 1:1 because of the way the grid and movements are generated to make sure they're the same on all screens. 
---
Description:
An 80X80 grid of tiles are scrambled, shuffled, shifted, streamed, transported,
conveyed, moved, deposited. 

There are 15 initial tile states and 5 color palettes. A set of 12 unique motion patterns
are generated for each piece. 
---
Acknowledgements:
This piece is inspired by Kim Asendorf, whose pixel-level algorithms I'm
transfixed by, and Ksawery Komputery, whose algorithmic tile-works I'm crazy
about. 
---
Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with P5.js 
December 2021, Germany
